TITLE: Jan. 6 Capitol riot committee won't let Trump turn testimony into a 'circus,' Cheney says
SUMMARY: Committee Vice Chairwoman Liz Cheney, R-Wyo., said Trump will not be able to turn his testimony into a "circus."

TITLE: Millions at risk of losing health insurance if U.S. ends Covid public health emergency in January
SUMMARY: When the public health emergency does end, HHS estimates up to 15 million people will be disenrolled from Medicare and the Children's Health Insurance Program.

TITLE: Here are the top Senate races to watch in the 2022 midterms
SUMMARY: The 2022 midterm elections occur on November 8, and a handful of make-or-break races will decide which party controls the Senate. Use this guide to sort them out and learn key facts about each candidate.

TITLE: Toymaker Mattel agrees to pay $3.5 million SEC fine for misstatements in 2017 earnings
SUMMARY: Toymaker Mattel will pay a $3.5 million fine for failing to accurately record its earnings, according to an SEC report.

TITLE: Crypto PACs backed by Sam Bankman-Fried, Scaramucci plan last-minute ad blitz for midterm elections
SUMMARY: Political action committees funded by cryptocurrency executives such as Sam Bankman-Fried are launching a last-minute ad blitz in the 2022 midterm elections.

TITLE: President Biden says 22 million people have signed up for student loan forgiveness
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden said Friday that 22 million people have registered for his administration's federal student loan relief program.

TITLE: Jan. 6 Capitol riot committee subpoenas former President Donald Trump
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump "personally orchestrated" efforts to reverse his loss to President Joe Biden, leaders of the Jan. 6 Capitol riot probe said.

TITLE: Biden predicts Democrats' odds will improve as the midterm elections approach, citing economic improvements
SUMMARY: Biden predicted that voters will swing back to favor Democrats again in the few remaining weeks before the midterm elections as concerns over the economy ease.

TITLE: U.S. Defense secretary speaks with Russian counterpart as war in Ukraine enters ninth month
SUMMARY: The last known instance of the two leaders speaking was in May.

TITLE: Steve Bannon sentenced to 4 months in jail for contempt of Congress
SUMMARY: Former top Trump White House advisor Steve Bannon was sentenced for defying a subpoena from the House probe of the Jan. 6 Capitol riot.

TITLE: Billionaire Ronald Lauder gives $1 million to GOP group supporting state candidates who questioned 2020 election results
SUMMARY: Billionaire Ronald Lauder gave $1 million to the Republican State Leadership Committee, which is supporting candidates who questioned the 2020 election results.

TITLE: Supreme Court rejects request to block Biden student loan debt forgiveness program
SUMMARY: The Biden administration program will cancel up to $20,000 in student loan debt for millions of people. A Wisconsin group asked the Supreme Court to block it.

TITLE: Sen. Lindsey Graham loses appeals court bid to stall testimony in Trump election interference probe
SUMMARY: A grand jury in Georgia is investigating Donald Trump for possible criminal interference in the 2020 presidential election, which he lost to President Joe Biden.

TITLE: Cryptocurrency service provider agrees to return $17 million to digital lender Celsius as it reorganizes in bankruptcy
SUMMARY: Prime Trust agreed  at a hearing at the U.S. Bankruptcy Court for the Southern District of New York on Thursday to return the money to settle a lawsuit.

TITLE: Robin Hood Foundation picks Goldman Sachs executive Dina Powell McCormick as new chair
SUMMARY: The Robin Hood Foundation has donated more than $3 billion over the last three decades to groups that fight poverty.

TITLE: Trump lashes out at judge who said former president knowingly pushed false voter fraud case
SUMMARY: U.S. District Judge David Carter ordered pro-Trump attorney John Eastman to turn over dozens of documents to the House probe of the Jan. 6 Capitol riot.

TITLE: Four U.S. states order a metaverse casino to halt sale of NFTs
SUMMARY: A metaverse casino was hit Thursday with a multistate emergency cease-and-desist order.

TITLE: Iran calls Western allegations that it supplied Russia with drones 'disappointing,' calls for peaceful resolution of war
SUMMARY: Moscow has carried out devastating drone strikes against what Ukraine said were civilian targets as well as critical infrastructure such as energy facilities.

TITLE: Biden administration awards $2.8 billion in grants for electric vehicle battery manufacturing
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden announced $2.8 billion worth of grants for twenty companies to produce batteries for electric vehicles in the United States.

TITLE: Judge says more of attorney John Eastman's emails about Trump election challenge must be given to Jan. 6 probe
SUMMARY: Eight of John Eastman's emails about Donald Trump's election challenge were subject to the "crime-fraud exception" to attorney-client privilege, the order said.

TITLE: Biden says oil companies should ramp up production and cut prices at the pump instead of buying back stock, paying dividends
SUMMARY: "You should not be using your profits to buy back stock or for dividends. Not now. Not while a war is raging," Biden said to U.S. energy companies.

TITLE: John Fetterman 'has no work restrictions' as he recovers from stroke, PA Senate hopeful's doctor says
SUMMARY: The doctor's assessment came as Fetterman's auditory processing ability has continued to draw questions about his health in the late stages of the campaign.

TITLE: UK's Suella Braverman resigns as interior minister after 43 days, former Transport Secretary Grant Shapps to replace her
SUMMARY: The news comes at a hugely turbulent time for the U.K. government, with Prime Minister Liz Truss under pressure to resign just two months into her premiership.

TITLE: Trump deposed in rape-defamation lawsuit by writer E. Jean Carroll
SUMMARY: Donald Trump also faces an expected state court lawsuit in November by writer E. Jean Carroll over her claim that he raped her in a New York department store.

TITLE: Biden to announce release of up to 15 million barrels of oil from Strategic Petroleum Reserve
SUMMARY: The goal of the latest release will be to extend the current SPR delivery program, which began this spring, through the month of December, the sources said.

TITLE: Biden to ask Congress to codify Roe v. Wade abortion rights protections if Democrats keep control
SUMMARY: Biden said he would ask lawmakers to codify the abortion rights protections in the Roe v. Wade decision if Democrats control Congress after the midterms.

TITLE: Georgia breaks first-day early voting record, nearly doubles figure from last midterms
SUMMARY: The early-voting data in Georgia comes three weeks before Election Day, with high-profile candidates such as Raphael Warnock and Herschel Walker on the ballot.

TITLE: French company fined $777 million and pleads guilty to paying ISIS as terror group killed Westerners
SUMMARY: Lafarge SA is settling U.S. criminal charges related to payments to terror group ISIS to maintain safety at a plant in Syria.

TITLE: Democrats in key Senate races have more cash to spend than Republicans in the final midterm push
SUMMARY: Democrats running in key 2022 midterm Senate races, including John Fetterman and Raphael Warnock, have more cash on hand than their Republican opponents.

TITLE: DOJ wants Steve Bannon jailed for 6 months for contempt of Congress, but ex-Trump aide asks for probation
SUMMARY: Federal prosecutors recommended Steve Bannon get six months in jail for defying a subpoena from the congressional probe of the Jan. 6 Capitol riot.
